name: r-classdiscovery

owner.description: Bioconda is a distribution of bioinformatics software realized as a channel for the versatile Conda package manager.
owner.name: bioconda

summary: Defines the classes used for "class discovery" problems in the OOMPA project (<http://oompa.r-forge.r-project.org/>). Class discovery primarily consists of unsupervised clustering methods with attempts to assess their statistical significance.
